article.headline: Samford 68, Tennessee Tech 65
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- With 21 points, Randall Gulina led Samford to a 68-65 victory over Tennessee Tech Tuesday night. Samford (7-6, 4-0 OVC) led 35-19 at the half, but Tennessee Tech (5-8, 1-3 OVC) shot 56.7 percent in the half versus Samford's 35.3 percent to bring the final score to a narrow three-point margin. But despite the hustle, the Golden Eagles never led in the second half. Travis Peterson had 16 points for Samford, and Joe Ross Merritt chipped in with ten points. Tennessee Tech was led by Amadi McKenzie who shared the game-high 21 points with Gulina. Belton Rivers added 20 points and Anthony Fisher helped out with 16 points and five assists. The Golden Eagles led 6-5 early on before Samford went on a 12-2 run to take a 17-8 advantage. Samford's biggest lead of the night was 18 points, three times late in the first half.
